        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 31 at 1:44PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 144 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southeast of Mule Creek, moving northwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mule Creek and Brushy Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
